<subSubSection id="60A6FC988630FF85FF47FEA81BCA1C68" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2803AF138630FF85FF47FEA81BCA1C68" blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FF47FEA81B7B1F49" bold="true" box="[199,315,258,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described by H. Aspöck &amp; U. 
<bibRefCitation id="4C2DD2E28630FF85FC62FEA81ECC1F48" author="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U." box="[994,1164,258,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" pagination="26 - 27" refId="ref4996" refString="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U. (1967) Agulla kaszabi nov. spec. (Insecta, Raphidiodea) aus der Mongolei. (Vorlaufige Beschreibung). Entomologisches Nachrichtenblatt, Wien, 14, 26 - 27." type="journal article" year="1967">Aspöck (1967)</bibRefCitation>
based on a single male specimen from Mt. Altai of Mongolia. Here 
<taxonomicName id="EFBCD4908630FF85FD1CFE8C19BA1F15" baseAuthorityName="H. Aspock &amp; U. Aspock" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[668,1018,294,321]" class="Insecta" family="Raphidiidae" genus="Mongoloraphidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Raphidioptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi" subGenus="Mongoloraphidia">
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FD1CFE8C19221F15" box="[668,866,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Mongoloraphidia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FCF4FE8D19D31F15" box="[884,915,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FC26FE8C19BA1F15" box="[934,1018,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">kaszabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="50ABEF838630FF85FB4CFE8C1F4F1F15" box="[1228,1295,294,320]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time based on the specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="EA7861F18630FF85FD95FEE0183B1F31" box="[533,635,330,356]" country="China" name="Xinjiang Uygur" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Xinjiang</collectingRegion>
. The identification of this additional male specimen as 
<taxonomicName id="EFBCD4908630FF85FB6AFEE11FDC1F31" baseAuthorityName="H. Aspock &amp; U. Aspock" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[1258,1436,330,357]" class="Insecta" family="Raphidiidae" genus="Mongoloraphidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Raphidioptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi" subGenus="Mongoloraphidia">
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FB6AFEE11F491F31" box="[1258,1289,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FA99FEE11F781F31" box="[1305,1336,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FAC8FEE01FDC1F31" box="[1352,1436,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">kaszabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be justified based on its male genital characters that are nearly identical to that of the 
<typeStatus id="F70711B18630FF85FB12FEC41EB41FDD" box="[1170,1268,366,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species (see H. Aspöck &amp; U. 
<bibRefCitation id="4C2DD2E28630FF85FE0DFE3818671FF9" author="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U." box="[397,551,402,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" pagination="26 - 27" refId="ref4996" refString="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U. (1967) Agulla kaszabi nov. spec. (Insecta, Raphidiodea) aus der Mongolei. (Vorlaufige Beschreibung). Entomologisches Nachrichtenblatt, Wien, 14, 26 - 27." type="journal article" year="1967">Aspöck 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1). However, there is another species, namely 
<taxonomicName id="EFBCD4908630FF85FBEFFE38183B1F85" authority="H. Aspock, U. Aspock &amp; Martynova, 1968" authorityName="H. Aspock, U. Aspock &amp; Martynova" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Raphidiidae" genus="Mongoloraphidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Raphidioptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sajanica">
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FBEFFE381FDC1FF9" box="[1135,1436,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">Mongoloraphidia sajanica</emphasis>
H. Aspöck, U. 
<bibRefCitation id="4C2DD2E28630FF85FEBEFE1C183B1F85" author="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U. &amp; Martynova, O. M." box="[318,635,438,465]" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" pagination="86 - 89" refId="ref5091" refString="Aspock, H., Aspock, U. &amp; Martynova, O. M. (1968) Neue Arten der Gattung Raphidia L. (Insecta, Raphidiodea) aus der Sowjet- Union (Vorlaufige Beschreibung). Entomologisches Nachrichtenblatt, Wien, 15, 86 - 89." type="journal article" year="1968">Aspöck &amp; Martynova, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EFBCD4908630FF85FBD6FE1D1F481F85" baseAuthorityName="H. Aspock &amp; U. Aspock" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[1110,1288,438,465]" class="Insecta" family="Raphidiidae" genus="Mongoloraphidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Raphidioptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kaszabi" subGenus="Mongoloraphidia">
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FBD6FE1D1E351F85" box="[1110,1141,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">M.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FB05FE1D1EE41F85" box="[1157,1188,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="1AC873018630FF85FB34FE1C1F481F85" box="[1204,1288,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="581">kaszabi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has geographically close distribution with the latter species. At present, it is not practical to clearly distinguish them as two independent species, and further investigation based on more specimens and molecular data is necessary to confirm if both are synonyms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
